       'grades_offense', 'longest', 'receptions', 'routes',

In [33]:
def scatter_1k(data1, data2): # function to show scatterplot of each correlation
    df_1ka = df_1k[[data1, '1,000 Yard Seasons']]
    df_0ka = df_0k[[data1, '1,000 Yard Seasons']]
    plt.figure(figsize = (5,5))
    plt.scatter(df_0ka[data1], df_0ka['1,000 Yard Seasons'], color= 'red' )
    plt.scatter(df_1ka[data1], df_1ka['1,000 Yard Seasons'], color= 'blue' )
    plt.title(f'1k yard Seasons by {data2}')
    plt.xlabel(data2)
    plt.ylabel("Number of 1k Yard seasons")
    plt.show()
